body_html:
I believe you. Let's reopen.

I noticed you're using TF 1.6. The tutorial points to wide_deep.py which had E2E tests added in tensorflow/models#3798 a few months after that release.

@kjancke could you please try the tutorial at head and let us know if it works? If it doesn't, then could you include a short minimal little shell script that reproduces the error? Something along the lines of:

virtualenv tf
source tf/bin/activate
pip install tensorflow
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tensorflow/models/master/official/wide_deep/wide_deep.py
python wide_deep.py ...

body:
I believe you. Let's reopen.

I noticed you're using TF 1.6. The [tutorial](https://www.tensorflow.org/tutorials/wide_and_deep) points to [wide_deep.py](https://github.com/tensorflow/models/commits/master/official/wide_deep/wide_deep.py) which had E2E tests added in https://github.com/tensorflow/models/pull/3798 a few months after that release.

@kjancke could you please try the tutorial at head and let us know if it works? If it doesn't, then could you include a short minimal little shell script that reproduces the error? Something along the lines of:

```sh
virtualenv tf
source tf/bin/activate
pip install tensorflow
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tensorflow/models/master/official/wide_deep/wide_deep.py
python wide_deep.py ...
```
